  "response": "Here are some tips to improve your English grammar:\n\n1. Study grammar rules\n- Use grammar books and online resources\n- Learn basic sentence structures\n- Understand verb tenses\n\n2. Read extensively\n- Books, newspapers, magazines\n- Notice how sentences are constructed\n- Learn grammar through context\n\n3. Practice writing\n- Write regularly\n- Keep a journal\n- Get feedback from native speakers or teachers\n\n4. Use online resources\n- Grammar websites\n- Language learning apps\n- YouTube grammar tutorials\n\n5. Take courses\n- Online grammar classes\n- Language exchange programs\n- English language courses\n\n6. Listen to native speakers\n- Podcasts\n- English-language movies and TV shows\n- Conversations\n\n7. Use grammar checking tools\n- Grammarly\n- Hemingway Editor\n- ProWritingAid\n\n8. Learn from your mistakes\n- Ask for corrections\n- Analyze your errors\n- Practice weak areas\n\n9. Study common grammar rules\n- Subject-verb agreement\n- Correct use of articles\n- Verb tenses\n- Punctuation\n\n10. Be patient and consistent\n- Learning takes time\n- Practice regularly\n- Don't get discouraged",
